<p class=\"western\">
    Make a POST request to the specified endpoint to create a company.     
</p>
<table width=\"100%\" class=\"endpoint-table\">
    <tr>
        <td width=\"25%\"><strong>Operation Name</strong></td>
        <td width=\"1%\">:</td>
        <td>GET</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td><strong>Production API Endpoint</strong></td>
        <td>:</td>
        <td valign=\"top\">https://skyapi.franconnect.net/company-management/v2/companies/{companyId}</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td><strong>UAT API Endpoint</strong></td>
        <td>:</td>
        <td valign=\"top\">https://skyapi.franconnectuat.net/company-management/v2/companies/{companyId} </td>
    </tr>
</table>The following items must be included in the header of the request:<ol>
    <li>
        <p>\"Authorization\" as the key and its value in the format \"Bearer access_token\". This access_token is
            generated as a part of authentication. Click <u><a href=\"#tag/Authentication\">here</a></u> for details on
            the steps to generate the access token.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
        <p>&ldquo;Content-Type&rdquo; as the key and its value in the format &ldquo;application/json&rdquo;.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
        <p>&ldquo;X-TenantId&rdquo; as the key and its value based on your FranConnect system&rsquo;s URL. Click <u><a
                    href=\"#tag/Authentication\">here</a></u>&nbsp;for details on identifying the
            &ldquo;X-TenantId&rdquo;.
        <p><img src=\"images/Create_Company.png\"></p>
    <p class=\"western\">
        Create a company in the system using fields and sections available on the primary details tab of that company. A list of default fields can be found in the request body schema below. Since your system configurations may include customized fields for building up a company profile, to retrieve all such custom fields, you will need to hit a query type endpoint on the entity details sub-module under Info Mgr module.
        
        <ol>
            <li>
                <b>Understanding Query Endpoints</b>: First, review the \"List of Field Names\" section in our documentation to understand how query endpoints are used. Since you are creating a company, you will be performing the CREATE operation. Proceed to the \"Retrieve Schema > Create\" section of our documentation.
            </li>
            <li>
                <b>Setting Module and Sub-Module</b>: Set the \"module\" value to \"fim\", which refers to the Info Manager module. Additionally, set the \"sub-module\" value to \"entity\".
            </li>
            <li>
                <b>Specifying Role Type</b>: Set the \"roleTypeForQuery\" to \"1\", indicating a corporate type user.
            </li>
            <li>
                <b>Defining Operation</b>: Set the \"operation\" to \"create\".
            </li>
        </ol>
        <p>
            <b>Identifying Custom Fields</b>: Custom fields in the response are formatted uniquely. They are a combination of the actual field's name and a random number, and they always begin with an underscore. For example, in the response below, you can identify two such custom fields: \"_faction74287762\" and \"_abn846032980\".
            <pre> <code>
                <fimEntity> <br>
                    <parentReferenceId>Parent referenceId(Mandatory)</parentReferenceId><br>
                    <entityType>Entity(New/Existing)(Default 'New')</entityType><br>
                    <fimTtEntityName>Name(Mandatory)</fimTtEntityName><br>
                    <exOwnerIDs>Owner(s)</exOwnerIDs><br>
                    <fimCbCountryOfFormation>Country of Formation/Residency</fimCbCountryOfFormation><br>
                    <fimDdDateOfFormation>Date of Formation(YYYY-MM-DD)</fimDdDateOfFormation><br>
                    <fimCbStateOfFormation>State of Formation/Residency</fimCbStateOfFormation><br>
                    <fimTtTaxpayer>Taxpayer ID/FEIN(PII Field)</fimTtTaxpayer><br>
                    <fimCbEntityType>Entity Type</fimCbEntityType><br>
                    <fimCbOtherEntityType><br>
                    This field will be considered if fimCbEntityType is 'Others'<br>
                    </fimCbOtherEntityType><br>
                    <_faction74287762>Faction</_faction74287762><br>
                    <_abn846032980>ABN</_abn846032980><br>
                    <fimEntityAreaMapping><br>
                    <areaID>Area / Region(s)</areaID><br>
                    </fimEntityAreaMapping><br>
                    </fimEntity><br>
                </code> 
            </pre>
        </p>
        <p>
            Please note that as long as you correctly enter mandatory fields during the company creation process, the company will be created successfully. However, if the data provided for non-mandatory fields is invalid, the system may generate warnings.
            
            Ensure that you refer to our API documentation for the specific field names and details required for creating a company.
        </p>
    </p>
